</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>What I think I have observed... all subjective, of course... is that skill goes up faster if you're within a zone of about 30 points below trivial to 5 points below trivial, then it slows down dramatically.<br />
<br />
If someone wants to try this, I suggest buying fresh fish and batwings in FP - both available on vendors - and combining in a spit or oven to make fishrolls, then examining the log to see where the skill point increases occurred.  Fishrolls trivialize at like 135 or so.  Unfortunately, this is a long slow boring haul and would have to be done multiple times with identical characters/buffs to be valid as a test.  Sounds like a lot of work to me.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=529003">Twoflower Tourist</a> - <a href="http://www.unionofpower.org">Union of Power</a><br />
62 Oracle<br />
