	<p>One rumor is that skill increases are more likely after a successful combine than an unsuccessful combine. As you are more likely to be successful if you are trying to make a potion that has trivial level 10 above your current skill than a potion that has trivial level 30 above your current skill, then you would be more likely to get a skill increase with the lower triv potion.<br />
<br />
Not sure if this is true, but it does seem to be the conventional wisdom.<br />
<br />
Argoth of Drinal</p>
	
	
	
	
	
